Dear Brendan,

Thank you for your time and thoughts the other day. I want to make a final appeal to you to let me keep working from Mexico. Below is an ennumeration of the software I have written for the company that I am still the person who knows the most about. If only for maintaining these tools that are central to the company product, it would be worth the effort to host me from Mexico, and all this knowledge would be put to good use.

* Review processing tool (improved it to make review processing faster and ergonomic --no mouse input needed)
* Translations priority system, interface with Google's Translation's toolkit (GTT)
* Change requests for hotel content
* Editor's priority tool (centralizes all tasks our editors must work on)
* XPhoto (simplifies creation of new photo types for front-end)
* AttributeValue (simplifies addition of variables associated to hotels and room objects, in wide use by many devs)
* Hotels bulk creation tool (has been used extensively to speed up the opening of new hotels)
* Support for dialects (American English, Brazilian Portuguese) on the website
* Automatic login from intranet to extranet (allows internal users to log in to the hotel's extranet without entering username and password).

I also consider your offer for an exit bonus to be generous, and I will also be happy to take it if you prefer this. In this case I will also want to make good on your offer of recommending me to the CTOs of our sister companies in the US, starting with OpenTable. I looked at the positions they offer and there is a good overlap in skills needed, except I'm not too fresh on Java. But I would have six months to brush up on it before joining them, if needed. Please let me know how to proceed, and thank you in advance.

Respectfully,

Claudio 



